. Decisions of the Complaints Commission
(1) The Complaints Commission or any of its panels may, after hearing the
parties to a complaint—
(a)order the offending party to publish an apology and correction in such
manner as the Commission may specify;
(b)order the return, repair, or replacement of any equipment or material
belonging to a journalist confiscated or destroyed;
(c)make any directive and declaration on freedom of expression;
(d)issue a public reprimand of the journalist or media enterprise involved;
(e)order the offending editor of the broadcast, print or on-line material
to publish the Commission’s decision in such manner as specified by
the Commission;
